								<h1 style="font-family:Times New Roman; "> <font color="maroon" >Depression Detection System </font></h1>
									<p style="font-family:Times New Roman; font-size:20px"><font color="black" >A depression detection system using image processing and text analysis is a computerized system that utilizes both visual and textual cues to identify symptoms of depression. The system is designed to analyze images and text from social media platforms and other sources to detect signs of depression. The image-processing component of the system uses computer vision algorithms to analyze facial expressions, body language, and other visual cues to identify signs of depression. Meanwhile, the text analysis component uses natural language processing techniques to analyze text from social media posts, messages, and other sources to detect indicators of depression. By combining these two approaches, the depression detection system can accurately identify individuals who may be at risk of depression or who may already be experiencing depressive symptoms. Once identified, these individuals can be connected with appropriate mental health resources and support. Overall, the depression detection system using image processing and text analysis is a promising tool for the early detection and intervention of depression. However, it's important to note that the system should not be used as a replacement for professional mental health diagnosis and treatment, but rather as a complement to existing approaches.</div>
								
